                        <tr><td>14</td><td>Clan God</td><td>Neelkanth Mahadev Ji</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>15</td><td>Salutation</td><td>Jai Raghunath Ji</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <h1>🕉️ Four Sacred Places (Dhams) of Badgujar Clan</h1>
            <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Machadi</strong> - The ancestral seat</li>
                    <li><strong>Devti</strong></li>
                    <li><strong>Koleshwar</strong></li>
                    <li><strong>Kakavadi</strong></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h1>🌿 Eight Branches of Badgujar Rajput Suryavansh Clan</h1>
            <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Rajora Badgujar</strong> (Rajoragrah)</li>
                    <li><strong>Sikarwar</strong> (Sikri)</li>
                    <li><strong>Khandara</strong> (Anupshahar, Bhodsi)</li>
                    <li><strong>Marad</strong> (Panipat, Karnel)</li>
                    <li><strong>Rayjada</strong> (Vidhisha, Bhenlsa)</li>
                    <li><strong>Munjwal</strong> (Samahda)</li>
                    <li><strong>Pokarna</strong> (Pokaran)</li>
                    <li><strong>Kannaujiya Badgujar</strong> (Surgaj, U.P.)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h1>⚔️ The Role of the Badgujars in Indian History</h1>
            <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                <p>The Badgujar Rajputs were not just rulers but also defenders of their land and culture. They played a pivotal role in resisting foreign invasions and maintaining regional stability during the reigns of the Marathas, Rajputs, and Mughals. Their military strategies and administrative skills ensured the prosperity of their territories, making them key players in the power dynamics of central and western India.</p>
            </div>

            <h1>🎨 Cultural and Social Contributions</h1>
            <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                <p>Beyond their military achievements, the Badgujar Rajputs made significant contributions to the cultural and social fabric of Madhya Pradesh. They built forts, palaces, and temples that stand as testaments to their architectural prowess. Their patronage of art, literature, and religious institutions helped preserve Rajputana traditions, which continue to influence the region's culture today.</p>
            </div>

            <h1>🌟 The Modern Legacy of the Badgujar Rajputs</h1>
            <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                <p>Today, the Badgujar Rajputs continue to honor their heritage while adapting to modern times. Many descendants are active in politics, administration, and social service, ensuring that the clan's legacy remains relevant. Historical estates like <strong>Dabla Ghosi</strong> serve as reminders of their glorious past, while cultural events and family records keep their traditions alive.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <p><strong>The Badgujar Rajputs of Madhya Pradesh have left an enduring legacy that transcends time.</strong> From their valiant battles and administrative excellence to their cultural contributions, their impact on the region's history is undeniable. The story of the Badgujar Rajputs is not just a chapter in Indian history but a testament to the enduring spirit of honor, courage, and resilience.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px; text-align: center;"><em>🙏 "Veer Bhogya Vasundhara" - The brave inherit the earth 🙏</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

